data.title: About Us
data.meta_site_name: Town of Emmet, Dodge County, WI
data.text:
Established in 1848, the Town of Emmet is a growing community located in south east Dodge County. Our current population is approximately 1300 residents. The town consists of many farms, numerous residential properties, industry, and a variety of business and commercial properties.

The City of Watertown is adjacent to the town and offers residents access to jobs, shopping, restaurants, schools, medical facilities and entertainment. The Town of Emmet is also located within commuting distance of Madison and Milwaukee; providing residents access to larger city amenities while enjoying small community living.

Town of Emmet residents also have access to a variety of outdoor recreation. A portion of The Glacial River Bike Trail is located within the township. The Wild Goose Trail is also located nearby. Residents also have access to nearby private and public golf courses. Lakes, rivers and woodlands within driving distance offer opportunities for hiking, boating, fishing, hunting and a variety of outdoor activities.
